President Biden spoke with Governor Tate Reeves, Senators Roger Wicker and Cindy Hyde-Smith, and Congressman Bennie Thompson of Mississippi to offer his condolences for the lives lost and the damage caused by the recent tornadoes and extreme weather in the state. He asked what assistance the people of Mississippi require and how he can support them. The President expressed his commitment to providing federal aid quickly and helping the affected communities recover. He also spoke with FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell, who will be visiting Mississippi to ensure a comprehensive federal response to those in need.